# ==========================================================================
# Line-ending policy — FORCE LF on checkout for every text file.
#
# Every script here runs in a Linux container (bash/perl), Git Bash, or
# PowerShell, all of which want LF. bash literally breaks on CRLF:
#   $'\r': command not found  /  set: -: invalid option  /  syntax error ... in\r
# and it silently corrupts the sandbox's copy of the butler hooks.
#
# The host is Windows with core.autocrlf=true, which would otherwise smudge CRLF
# into the working tree on every checkout / merge / branch-switch (that is
# exactly how the butler hooks got broken once). `eol=lf` overrides autocrlf so
# this can never recur. Binary files are auto-detected by `text=auto` and left
# untouched.
# ==========================================================================
* text=auto eol=lf

# Explicit for the executable / script types that HARD-break on CRLF
# (defense in depth + documents intent).
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf
*.pl    text eol=lf
*.pm    text eol=lf
*.t     text eol=lf
*.ps1   text eol=lf
Containerfile text eol=lf
